);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$a1 = random(2,6,2);
$x1 = 3.14159265/6;
$y1 = $a1/2;
$m1 = $a1*sqrt(3)/2;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$PAR
Find the equation of the tangent line to the curve
 \( y =   $a1 \sin x \)
at the point \( ( \pi/6 , $y1) \).
$PAR
The equation of this tangent line can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \) where
$PAR
\( m = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}
$PAR
and \( b = \) \{ans_rule(20) \}
EOT

$ans = $m1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

$ans = $y1 -$m1*$x1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

